title: Missing models during client generation

labels.name: model
labels.description: Related to swagger generate model command

body:
## Problem statement

Generated client library fails to build due to missing models that aren't generated.

There's a `models` modules referenced in one of the generated files (`client/webhooks/webhooks_create_responses.go`), but it's not generated, therefore not available.

No matter what combination of command line flags I use I'm not able to generate the missing models. The spec validates successfully using `swagger validate ...` but not sure if there's perhaps something odd about it.

Any help or pointers would be greatly appreciated, thanks.

## Swagger specification

https://api.cloudsmith.io/?format=openapi

## Steps to reproduce

Create the following files:

`go.mod`

```
module github.com/cloudsmith-io/cloudsmith-go

go 1.14
```

`main.go`

```go
package main

import "github.com/cloudsmith-io/cloudsmith-go/client"

func main {
	client.New(nil, nil)
}
```

Then run:

```
curl -o swagger.json "https://api.cloudsmith.io/?format=openapi"
swagger generate client -f swagger.json
go build
```

Results in the output:

